001package gust.backend.transport;
002
003import javax.annotation.Nonnull;
004import javax.annotation.Nullable;
005import java.util.Optional;
006
007
008/** Enumerates Google Cloud services with built-in managed transport support. */
009public enum GoogleService {
010  /** Google Cloud Pub-Sub (token: <pre>pubsub</pre>). */
011  PUBSUB("pubsub", null),
012
013  /** Google Cloud Storage (token: <pre>storage</pre>). */
014  STORAGE("storage", null),
015
016  /** Google Cloud Firestore (token: <pre>firestore</pre>) */
017  FIRESTORE("firestore", null);
018
019  /** Prefix at which the specified service may be configured. */
020  private final @Nonnull String token;
021
022  /** Config bindings class for the provided service. */
023  private final @Nullable Class<GoogleTransportConfig> configType;
024
025  /**
026   * Private constructor.
027   *
028   * @param token Configuration binding prefix.
029   * @param configType Configuration class type.
030   */
031  GoogleService(@Nonnull String token,
032                @Nullable Class<GoogleTransportConfig> configType) {
033    this.token = token;
034    this.configType = configType;
035  }
036
037  // -- Getters -- //
038  /**
039   * @return Prefix at which the specified service can be configured.
040   */
041  public @Nonnull String getToken() {
042    return token;
043  }
044
045  /**
046   * @return Configuration bindings class for the provided service, if supported.
047   */
048  public @Nonnull Optional<Class<GoogleTransportConfig>> getConfigType() {
049    if (configType == null)
050      return Optional.empty();
051    return Optional.of(configType);
052  }
053}
